They both have eyes to see,
ears to hear, a mouth to eat, a heart and lungs to breathe, both have consciousness and awareness, and yet most only see and care about the dog. There is no difference between these two animals, they are both sentient ANIMALS. We are living in times where we don’t need to exploit, kill and eat animals to survive.
We all say we love them, so let’s live in alignment with that love.
Be kind to all of them 🍃
~

Despite Isabel’s happy & loving personality, she came into the shelter in very sad shape in early August. With TLC, she is recovering very well and READY to find a FAMILY who will CHERISH her!! Please help us to spread the word about this sweet girl or come #adopt her today!
*Blue/medically alerted for geriatric, dermatitis, hair loss, weak gait.*

Meet Jax - He was originally abandoned near downtown @eugene.or brought into our care at @greenhillhumane for almost 2 months before being adopted earlier this year. Here's what his family has to say - "We are loving our new friend... he is awesome. He is very communicative and lets us know when his bowl is empty. He loves to play and he loves to snuggle. He is adorable...sweet...and in three short weeks has become the living soul of our home. He has this cute thing he does when he is snuggling...if I stop petting him or he wants me to wake up...he extends his arm and drags his paw across my face with a little claw extended to get my attention. He is ok when I grab his paw and hold it. I think he just wants the connection. The adoption process was great and I was impressed with the love that is present in what could be a sad environment. Thank you for all that you do at the shelter; we are all in this together." We agree - we are all in this together! If you'd like to help us care for abandoned animals like Jax, please consider making a tax-deductible year-end gift - your support helps us provide safe shelter, healthy food, medical care and reunion / adoption services for approximately 3,000 lost and homeless animals each year.
